        <abstract> 
<p>A reader of <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> offers two items: 1. Masters observed a pericardial fold in humans and other mammals which is a vestigial left superior vena cava;</p>  
<p>2. JM suggests the frenum of the human penis became necessary for <hi rend="italic">vis-à-vis</hi> copulation when man became bipedal.</p> 
        </abstract>
